PortList.name: PortList
PortList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

VlanIndex.name: VlanIndex
VlanIndex.description: A value used to index per-VLAN tables: values of 0 and 4095 are not permitted; if the value is between 1 and 4094 inclusive, it represents an IEEE 802.1Q VLAN-ID with global scope within a given bridged domain (see VlanId textual convention). If the value is greater than 4095 then it represents a VLAN with scope local to the particular agent, i.e. one without a global VLAN-ID assigned to it. Such VLANs are outside the scope of IEEE 802.1Q but it is convenient to be able to manage them in the same way using this MIB.

DropDirection.name: DropDirection
DropDirection.description: Representing the direction of dropping packets, if applicable.

hpnicfifXXEntry.name: hpnicfifXXEntry
hpnicfifXXEntry.description: Entries of extended interface information table.

hpnicfifUnBoundPort.name: hpnicfifUnBoundPort
hpnicfifUnBoundPort.description: Whether it is the unbound port. (true indicates that the port is the main port of the aggregation or the port does not participate in the aggregation.)

hpnicfifISPhyPort.name: hpnicfifISPhyPort
hpnicfifISPhyPort.description: Whether it is a physical interface.

hpnicfifAggregatePort.name: hpnicfifAggregatePort
hpnicfifAggregatePort.description: Whether it is the aggregated port. (if the port participates in the aggregation, this value is true.)

hpnicfifMirrorPort.name: hpnicfifMirrorPort
hpnicfifMirrorPort.description: Whether it is a mirror port.

hpnicfifVLANType.name: hpnicfifVLANType
hpnicfifVLANType.description: port vlan types. hybrid (3) port can carry multiple VLANs. If fabric function is supported, fabric(4) means the port is a fabric port.

hpnicfifMcastControl.name: hpnicfifMcastControl
hpnicfifMcastControl.description: Broadcast storm suppression with the step length of 1, ranging from 0 to 100 percent. In some products the step is 5, ranging from 0 to 100.

hpnicfifSrcMacControl.name: hpnicfifSrcMacControl
hpnicfifSrcMacControl.description: Whether to filter by source MAC address.

hpnicfifClearStat.name: hpnicfifClearStat
hpnicfifClearStat.description: Clear specify port statistics. Operation read is not supported.

hpnicfifXXBasePortIndex.name: hpnicfifXXBasePortIndex
hpnicfifXXBasePortIndex.description: Index number of the port and the first port index of the device is 1.

hpnicfifPpsMcastControl.name: hpnicfifPpsMcastControl
hpnicfifPpsMcastControl.description: The broadcast suppression with pps(packet per second) type. The max value is determined by the port type and product.

hpnicfifPpsBcastDisValControl.name: hpnicfifPpsBcastDisValControl
hpnicfifPpsBcastDisValControl.description: Control the port's pps(packet per second) broadcast suppression. When the port is enabled, its pps broadcast suppression value is the global disperse value, and when disabled, it doesn't suppress broadcast.

hpnicfifUniSuppressionStep.name: hpnicfifUniSuppressionStep
hpnicfifUniSuppressionStep.description: The step of unicast suppression in ratio mode.

hpnicfifPpsUniSuppressionMax.name: hpnicfifPpsUniSuppressionMax
hpnicfifPpsUniSuppressionMax.description: The max pps(packet per second) value of unicast suppression in pps mode.

hpnicfifMulSuppressionStep.name: hpnicfifMulSuppressionStep
hpnicfifMulSuppressionStep.description: The step of multicast suppression in ratio mode.

hpnicfifPpsMulSuppressionMax.name: hpnicfifPpsMulSuppressionMax
hpnicfifPpsMulSuppressionMax.description: The max pps(packet per second) value of multicast suppression in pps mode.

hpnicfifUniSuppression.name: hpnicfifUniSuppression
hpnicfifUniSuppression.description: The unicast suppression with the ranging from 0 to 100 percent in ratio mode. The step is determined by hpnicfifUniSuppressionStep.

hpnicfifPpsUniSuppression.name: hpnicfifPpsUniSuppression
hpnicfifPpsUniSuppression.description: The unicast suppression in pps(packet per second) mode. The max value is determined by hpnicfifPpsUniSuppressionMax.

hpnicfifMulSuppression.name: hpnicfifMulSuppression
hpnicfifMulSuppression.description: The multicast suppression with ranging from 0 to 100 percent in ratio mode. The step is determined by hpnicfifMulSuppressionStep.

hpnicfifPpsMulSuppression.name: hpnicfifPpsMulSuppression
hpnicfifPpsMulSuppression.description: The multicast suppression in pps(packet per second) mode. The max pps value is determined by hpnicfifPpsMulSuppressionMax.

hpnicfifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax.name: hpnicfifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax
hpnicfifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax.description: The maximum value of the multicast suppression with bandwidth-based(Mbps) that a port can be configured.

hpnicfifBMbpsMulSuppression.name: hpnicfifBMbpsMulSuppression
hpnicfifBMbpsMulSuppression.description: With bandwidth-based multicast suppression, the bandwidth is measured in Mbps. The upper limit of the multicast suppession with bandwidth-based(Mbps) is the value of hpnicfifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax in the entry. The default value of hpnicfifBMbpsMulSuppression is the value of hpnicfifBMbpsMulSuppressionMax.

hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax.name: hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax
hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax.description: The maximum value of the multicast suppression with bandwidth-based(Kbps) that a port can be configured.

hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppressionStep.name: hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppressionStep
hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppressionStep.description: The step of multicast suppression with bandwidth-based(Kbps).

hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppression.name: hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppression
hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppression.description: With bandwidth-based multicast suppression, the bandwidth is measured in Kbps. The upper limit of the multicast suppession with bandwidth-based(Kbps) is the value of hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax in the entry. The value of hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppression must be multiple of the value of hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppressionStep. The default value of hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppression is the value of hpnicfifBKbpsMulSuppressionMax.

hpnicfifUnknownPacketDropMul.name: hpnicfifUnknownPacketDropMul
hpnicfifUnknownPacketDropMul.description: Control the port's unknown-multicast packets drop. When inbound direction is enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-multicast packets in inbound direction. When outbound direction is enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-multicast packets in outbound direction. When both directions are enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-multicast packets in both inbound and outbound directions.

hpnicfifUnknownPacketDropUni.name: hpnicfifUnknownPacketDropUni
hpnicfifUnknownPacketDropUni.description: Control the port's unknown-unicast packets drop. When inbound direction is enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-unicast packets in inbound direction. When outbound direction is enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-unicast packets in outbound direction. When both directions are enabled on this port, the port will drop unknown-unicast packets in both inbound and outbound directions.

hpnicfifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax.name: hpnicfifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax
hpnicfifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax.description: The maximum value of the unicast suppression with bandwidth-based (Mbps) that a port can be configured.

hpnicfifBMbpsUniSuppression.name: hpnicfifBMbpsUniSuppression
hpnicfifBMbpsUniSuppression.description: With bandwidth-based Unicast suppression, the bandwidth is measured in Mbps. The upper limit of the unicast suppession with bandwidth-based(Mbps) is the value of hpnicfifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax in the entry. The default value of hpnicfifBMbpsUniSuppression is the value of hpnicfifBMbpsUniSuppressionMax.

hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax.name: hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax
hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax.description: The maximum value of the unicast suppression with bandwidth-based (Kbps) that a port can be configured.

hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppressionStep.name: hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppressionStep
hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppressionStep.description: The step of unicast suppression with bandwidth-based(Kbps).

hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppression.name: hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppression
hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppression.description: With bandwidth-based unicast suppression, the bandwidth is measured in Kbps. The upper limit of the unicast suppession with bandwidth-based(Kbps) is the value of hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax in the entry. The value of hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppression must be multiple of the value of hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppressionStep. The default value of hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppression is the value of hpnicfifBKbpsUniSuppressionMax.

hpnicfifOutPayloadOctets.name: hpnicfifOutPayloadOctets
hpnicfifOutPayloadOctets.description: The actual output octets of the interface.

hpnicfifInPayloadOctets.name: hpnicfifInPayloadOctets
hpnicfifInPayloadOctets.description: The actual input octets of the interface.

hpnicfifInErrorPktsRate.name: hpnicfifInErrorPktsRate
hpnicfifInErrorPktsRate.description: The rate of inbound error packets on the interface.

hpnicfifInPkts.name: hpnicfifInPkts
hpnicfifInPkts.description: The number of packets received on the interface.

hpnicfifInNormalPkts.name: hpnicfifInNormalPkts
hpnicfifInNormalPkts.description: The number of normal packets received on the interface.

hpnicfifOutPkts.name: hpnicfifOutPkts
hpnicfifOutPkts.description: The number of packets sent on the interface.

hpnicfifAggregatePortIndex.name: hpnicfifAggregatePortIndex
hpnicfifAggregatePortIndex.description: Index number of the main aggregated port.

hpnicfifAggregateModel.name: hpnicfifAggregateModel
hpnicfifAggregateModel.description: Load sharing mode for the port aggregation.

hpnicfifAggregateOperStatus.name: hpnicfifAggregateOperStatus
hpnicfifAggregateOperStatus.description: Current operation status of the row.

hpnicfifHybridTaggedVlanListLow.name: hpnicfifHybridTaggedVlanListLow
hpnicfifHybridTaggedVlanListLow.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each tagged VLAN of the hybrid port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is tagged in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not tagged if its bit has a value of '0'.

hpnicfifHybridTaggedVlanListHigh.name: hpnicfifHybridTaggedVlanListHigh
hpnicfifHybridTaggedVlanListHigh.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 2049 through 2056, the second octet specifying VLANs 2057 through 2064, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each tagged VLAN of the hybrid port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is tagged in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not tagged if its bit has a value of '0'.

hpnicfifHybridUnTaggedVlanListLow.name: hpnicfifHybridUnTaggedVlanListLow
hpnicfifHybridUnTaggedVlanListLow.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each untagged VLAN of the hybrid port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is untagged in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not untagged if its bit has a value of '0'.

hpnicfifHybridUnTaggedVlanListHigh.name: hpnicfifHybridUnTaggedVlanListHigh
hpnicfifHybridUnTaggedVlanListHigh.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 2049 through 2056, the second octet specifying VLANs 2057 through 2064, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each untagged VLAN of the hybrid port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is untagged in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not untagged if its bit has a value of '0'.

hpnicfifComboPortIndex.name: hpnicfifComboPortIndex
hpnicfifComboPortIndex.description: The combo-port interface index. Its value is the same as the value of ifIndex in ifTable, but only includes indexes of the combo-port interfaces.

hpnicfifComboPortCurActive.name: hpnicfifComboPortCurActive
hpnicfifComboPortCurActive.description: Current active interface of combo interfaces. The value 'fiber' means the interface with fiber connector of the pair of combo-port interfaces is active. The value 'copper' means the interface with copper connector of the pair is active. The value 'na' means not supported.

hpnicfifPktBufFree.name: hpnicfifPktBufFree
hpnicfifPktBufFree.description: The number of packet buffers available for the interface.

hpnicfifPktBufInit.name: hpnicfifPktBufInit
hpnicfifPktBufInit.description: The number of packet buffers allocated when the interface was created.

hpnicfifPktBufMin.name: hpnicfifPktBufMin
hpnicfifPktBufMin.description: The smallest number of packet buffers available for the interface.

hpnicfifPktBufMiss.name: hpnicfifPktBufMiss
hpnicfifPktBufMiss.description: The number of times that the interface failed to obtain a packet buffer. Failure to obtain a buffer indicates that buffers were busy.

hpnicfSwitchPortMax.name: hpnicfSwitchPortMax
hpnicfSwitchPortMax.description: Max ports that this switch includes.

hpnicfifVLANTrunkStatusTable.name: hpnicfifVLANTrunkStatusTable
hpnicfifVLANTrunkStatusTable.description: Gvrp attributes on the VlanTrunk port.

hpnicfifVLANTrunkStatusEntry.name: hpnicfifVLANTrunkStatusEntry
hpnicfifVLANTrunkStatusEntry.description: Gvrp attributes on the VlanTrunk port.

hpnicfifVLANTrunkIndex.name: hpnicfifVLANTrunkIndex
hpnicfifVLANTrunkIndex.description: Index number of the VLANTrunk interface.

hpnicfifVLANTrunkGvrpRegistration.name: hpnicfifVLANTrunkGvrpRegistration
hpnicfifVLANTrunkGvrpRegistration.description: GVRP registration information normal: This is the default configuration. Allow create, register and unregister vlans dynamiclly at this port. fixed: Aallow create and register vlan manually at this port. Prevent from unregistering vlans or registering known vlans of this port at another trunk port. forbidden: Unregister all vlans but vlan 1, forbid to create or register any other vlans at this port.

hpnicfifVLANTrunkPassListLow.name: hpnicfifVLANTrunkPassListLow
hpnicfifVLANTrunkPassListLow.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each actually passed VLAN of the trunk port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is actually passed in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not actually passed if its bit has a value of '0'.

hpnicfifVLANTrunkPassListHigh.name: hpnicfifVLANTrunkPassListHigh
hpnicfifVLANTrunkPassListHigh.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 2049 through 2056, the second octet specifying VLANs 2057 through 2064, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each actually passed VLAN of the trunk port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is actually passed in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not actually passed if its bit has a value of '0'.

hpnicfifVLANTrunkAllowListLow.name: hpnicfifVLANTrunkAllowListLow
hpnicfifVLANTrunkAllowListLow.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLANs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each allowed VLAN of the trunk port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is allowed in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not allowed if its bit has a value of '0'.

hpnicfifVLANTrunkAllowListHigh.name: hpnicfifVLANTrunkAllowListHigh
hpnicfifVLANTrunkAllowListHigh.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLANs 2049 through 2056, the second octet specifying VLANs 2057 through 2064, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN, and the least significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN. Thus, each allowed VLAN of the trunk port is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is allowed in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not allowed if its bit has a value of '0'.

hpnicfethernetEntry.name: hpnicfethernetEntry
hpnicfethernetEntry.description: Entries of Ethernet port attribute table

hpnicfifEthernetMdi.name: hpnicfifEthernetMdi
hpnicfifEthernetMdi.description: Type of the line connected to the port. MDI-II (straight-through cable): 1 MDI-X (crossover cable): 2 MDI-AUTO (auto-sensing): 3

hpnicfMaxMacLearn.name: hpnicfMaxMacLearn
hpnicfMaxMacLearn.description: The maximum number of MAC addresses that the port can learn. The value -1 means that the number of Mac addresses that the port can learn is unlimited.

hpnicfifMacAddressLearn.name: hpnicfifMacAddressLearn
hpnicfifMacAddressLearn.description: This object indicates if the interface is allowed to learn mac address. eanbled(1) means the interface can learn mac address, otherwise disabled(2) can be set.

hpnicfifEthernetTest.name: hpnicfifEthernetTest
hpnicfifEthernetTest.description: Test this interface. The actual testing will be different according to products. Read operation not supported.

hpnicfifMacAddrLearnMode.name: hpnicfifMacAddrLearnMode
hpnicfifMacAddrLearnMode.description: Status indicates mac address learn mode of the interface. IVL(1) means independent VLAN learning. SVL means shared VLAN learning.

hpnicfifEthernetFlowInterval.name: hpnicfifEthernetFlowInterval
hpnicfifEthernetFlowInterval.description: Set flow interval of the ethernet. The NMS should set value to integer which is a multiple of 5.

hpnicfifEthernetIsolate.name: hpnicfifEthernetIsolate
hpnicfifEthernetIsolate.description: Isolate group means that all ports in the same isolate group can not send and receive packets each other. Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight isolate groups, with the first octet specifying isolate groups 1 through 8, the second octet specifying isolate groups 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the leftmost bit is the first bit. the first bit represents the lowest numbered isolate group, and the last bit represents the highest numbered isolate group. one port can belong to more than one isolate group. Thus, each isolate group is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1', then that isolate group includes this port; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. for example, the first octet is '10000100' means that the port is included in the isolate group 1 and isolate group 6.

hpnicfifVlanVPNTPID.name: hpnicfifVlanVPNTPID
hpnicfifVlanVPNTPID.description: Port based Vlan VPN TPID(Tag Protocol Indentifier), default value is 0x8100. Please refer to hpnicfVlanVPNTPIDMode to get more information.

hpnicfifIsolateGroupID.name: hpnicfifIsolateGroupID
hpnicfifIsolateGroupID.description: Isolate group identifier. Value zero means this interface does not belong to any isolate group.

hpnicfifisUplinkPort.name: hpnicfifisUplinkPort
hpnicfifisUplinkPort.description: Ethernet uplink status, default value is 2.

hpnicfifEthernetAutoSpeedMask.name: hpnicfifEthernetAutoSpeedMask
hpnicfifEthernetAutoSpeedMask.description: This object specifies which kinds of speed mode can be negotiated. Each bit corresponds to a kind of speed mode. If the value of a bit is '1', it means the corresponding speed mode is negotiable on the port. Otherwise the negotiation for that kind of speed mode is not supported on this port. If there are several negotiable speed modes, all bits for them are '1'. For example, if the speed mode 's10M' and 's1000M' can be negotiable, the value of this object is 0xA0.

hpnicfifEthernetAutoSpeed.name: hpnicfifEthernetAutoSpeed
hpnicfifEthernetAutoSpeed.description: This object indicates which kinds of speed mode are negotiable on this port. Only when a bit of hpnicfifEthernetAutoSpeedMask is '1', the corresponding bit of this object can be set to '1', indicating the corresponding speed mode is negotiable. For example, if the value of hpnicfifEthernetAutoSpeedMask is 0xA0, which indicates speed mode 's10M' and 's1000M' are negotiable, the possible value of this object should be one of the four values (0x00, 0x20, 0x80 and 0xA0). If the value of hpnicfifEthernetSpeed is not 'auto', the value of this object is insignificant and should be ignored. The value length of this object should be as long as that of hpnicfifEthernetAutoSpeedMask.

hpnicfIsolateGroupMax.name: hpnicfIsolateGroupMax
hpnicfIsolateGroupMax.description: Max isolate group that this device support, the value is zero means that the device does not support isolate group.

hpnicfGlobalBroadcastMaxPps.name: hpnicfGlobalBroadcastMaxPps
hpnicfGlobalBroadcastMaxPps.description: The global max packets per second. When it is set, the value of BroadcastMaxPps in all ports will be changed to that setting.

hpnicfGlobalBroadcastMaxRatio.name: hpnicfGlobalBroadcastMaxRatio
hpnicfGlobalBroadcastMaxRatio.description: The global max-ratio of broadcast from 0 to 100 percent. When it is set, the value of BroadcastMaxRatio in all ports will be changed to that setting.

hpnicfVlanVPNTPIDMode.name: hpnicfVlanVPNTPIDMode
hpnicfVlanVPNTPIDMode.description: Vlan VPN TPID mode. The value 'port-based' means VLAN VPN TPID value would be set based on port via hpnicfifVlanVPNTPID. In this situation, hpnicfVlanVPNTPID is meaningless and always return 0x8100. The value 'global' means VLAN VPN TPID value should be set globally via hpnicfVlanVPNTPID. In this situation, hpnicfifVlanVPNTPID in hpnicfethernetTable has the same value with hpnicfVlanVPNTPID.

hpnicfVlanVPNTPID.name: hpnicfVlanVPNTPID
hpnicfVlanVPNTPID.description: Global Vlan VPN TPID(Tag Protocol Indentifier), default value is 0x8100.

hpnicfPortIsolateGroupIndex.name: hpnicfPortIsolateGroupIndex
hpnicfPortIsolateGroupIndex.description: Port isolate group identifier. The index of the hpnicfPortIsolateGroupTable. The value ranges from 1 to the limit of isolate group quantity.

hpnicfPortIsolateUplinkIfIndex.name: hpnicfPortIsolateUplinkIfIndex
hpnicfPortIsolateUplinkIfIndex.description: Index number of the uplink interface.

hpnicfPortIsolateGroupRowStatus.name: hpnicfPortIsolateGroupRowStatus
hpnicfPortIsolateGroupRowStatus.description: Current operation status of the row.

hpnicfPortIsolateGroupDescription.name: hpnicfPortIsolateGroupDescription
hpnicfPortIsolateGroupDescription.description: Port isolate group description, default value is zero-length string.

hpnicfMaxMacLearnRange.name: hpnicfMaxMacLearnRange
hpnicfMaxMacLearnRange.description: The maximum number of MAC address that the port supports.

hpnicfifPortProtocolStatTable.name: hpnicfifPortProtocolStatTable
hpnicfifPortProtocolStatTable.description: This table contains objects of port statistics information based on IPv4 and IPv6 protocols.

hpnicfifIPv4InOctets.name: hpnicfifIPv4InOctets
hpnicfifIPv4InOctets.description: Number of octets based on IPv4 received on the interface.

hpnicfifIPv4InUcastPkts.name: hpnicfifIPv4InUcastPkts
hpnicfifIPv4InUcastPkts.description: Number of unicast packets based on IPv4 received on the interface.

hpnicfifIPv4InMultiPkts.name: hpnicfifIPv4InMultiPkts
hpnicfifIPv4InMultiPkts.description: Number of multicast packets based on IPv4 received on the interface.

hpnicfifIPv4InBroadcastPkts.name: hpnicfifIPv4InBroadcastPkts
hpnicfifIPv4InBroadcastPkts.description: Number of broadcast packets based on IPv4 received on the interface.

hpnicfifIPv4InDiscards.name: hpnicfifIPv4InDiscards
hpnicfifIPv4InDiscards.description: Number of discard packets based on IPv4 received on the interface.

hpnicfifIPv4InErrors.name: hpnicfifIPv4InErrors
hpnicfifIPv4InErrors.description: Number of error packets based on IPv4 received on the interface.

hpnicfifIPv4OutOctets.name: hpnicfifIPv4OutOctets
hpnicfifIPv4OutOctets.description: Number of octets based on IPv4 transmitted out of the interface.

hpnicfifIPv4OutUcastPkts.name: hpnicfifIPv4OutUcastPkts
hpnicfifIPv4OutUcastPkts.description: Number of unicast packets based on IPv4 transmitted out of the interface.

hpnicfifIPv4OutMultiPkts.name: hpnicfifIPv4OutMultiPkts
hpnicfifIPv4OutMultiPkts.description: Number of multicast packets based on IPv4 transmitted out of the interface.

hpnicfifIPv4OutBroadcastPkts.name: hpnicfifIPv4OutBroadcastPkts
hpnicfifIPv4OutBroadcastPkts.description: Number of broadcast packets based on IPv4 transmitted out of the interface.

hpnicfifIPv4OutDiscards.name: hpnicfifIPv4OutDiscards
hpnicfifIPv4OutDiscards.description: Number of discard packets based on IPv4 transmitted out of the interface.

hpnicfifIPv4OutErrors.name: hpnicfifIPv4OutErrors
hpnicfifIPv4OutErrors.description: Number of error packets based on IPv4 transmitted out of the interface.

hpnicfifIPv6InOctets.name: hpnicfifIPv6InOctets
hpnicfifIPv6InOctets.description: Number of octets based on IPv6 received on the interface.

hpnicfifIPv6InUcastPkts.name: hpnicfifIPv6InUcastPkts
hpnicfifIPv6InUcastPkts.description: Number of unicast packets based on IPv6 received on the interface.

hpnicfifIPv6InMultiPkts.name: hpnicfifIPv6InMultiPkts
hpnicfifIPv6InMultiPkts.description: Number of multicast packets based on IPv6 received on the interface.

hpnicfifIPv6InAnycastPkts.name: hpnicfifIPv6InAnycastPkts
hpnicfifIPv6InAnycastPkts.description: Number of anycast packets based on IPv6 received on the interface.

hpnicfifIPv6InDiscards.name: hpnicfifIPv6InDiscards
hpnicfifIPv6InDiscards.description: Number of discard packets based on IPv6 received on the interface.

hpnicfifIPv6InErrors.name: hpnicfifIPv6InErrors
hpnicfifIPv6InErrors.description: Number of error packets based on IPv6 received on the interface.

hpnicfifIPv6OutOctets.name: hpnicfifIPv6OutOctets
hpnicfifIPv6OutOctets.description: Number of octets based on IPv6 transmitted of the interface.

hpnicfifIPv6OutUcastPkts.name: hpnicfifIPv6OutUcastPkts
